tr.th: Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us

tr.td: The patient shows elevated creatinine, proteinuria, glucosuria, ketonuria, and bilirubinuria, with low urine specific gravity and abnormal urine appearance, suggesting impaired renal function and possible tubular damage. Blood glucose and HbA1c are not elevated, making diabetes less likely. Urine findings may indicate underlying renal pathology (e.g., glomerulonephritis, tubular disorder) and possible liver involvement. Recommend further nephrological and hepatological evaluation.
